Global Inorganic Fiberglass Yarn Market Insights
Inorganic Fiberglass Yarn Market size was valued at USD 1.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 2.8 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 8.6% from 2024 to 2030.

Inorganic Fiberglass Yarn Market Overview
The global inorganic fiberglass yarn market size was valued at USD 4.67 billion in 2024 and is expected to grow at a CAGR of 5.2% from 2025 to 2032. The increasing demand for lightweight and durable materials across various industries, including automotive, aerospace, and construction, is driving market growth. The need for high-strength composites and fire-resistant materials in industrial applications is also boosting market expansion. Fiberglass yarn is being increasingly used in electrical insulation, woven fabrics, and as a reinforcing agent in composite materials. This growth is complemented by advancements in manufacturing technologies that improve the performance of fiberglass products, thereby opening new market opportunities.

